<item>
            <title>[LU-17526] obdfilter-survey test_1a: 10.240.41.235:lustre-OST0001 10.240.41.235:lustre-OST0002: command not found</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17526</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Guillaume Courrier &amp;lt;guillaume.courrier@cea.fr&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/008b7f1f-670c-4a26-987a-97b6c736a901&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/008b7f1f-670c-4a26-987a-97b6c736a901&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;test_1a failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;/usr/bin/obdfilter-survey failed: 127
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Test session details:&lt;br/&gt;
clients: &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/101954&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/101954&lt;/a&gt; - 4.18.0-477.27.1.el8_8.x86_64&lt;br/&gt;
servers: &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/101954&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/101954&lt;/a&gt; - 4.18.0-477.27.1.el8_lustre.x86_64&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The format of lctl get_param osc.lustre-OST0000-osc-MDT0000.import was changed by &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10391&quot; title=&quot;LNET: Support IPv6&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-10391&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-10391&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to make it valid YAML but the function get_targets assumed that the value of current_connection did not contain extra &quot;&quot; around the NID. Therefore, a NID like &quot;0@lo&quot; would be interpreted by the function get_targets as &quot;0 instead of simply 0. The extra &quot; is confusing bash when running the command obdfilter-survey which make the test fail.&lt;/p&gt;







&lt;p&gt;VVVVVVV DO NOT REMOVE LINES BELOW, Added by Maloo for auto-association VVVVVVV&lt;br/&gt;
obdfilter-survey test_1a - /usr/bin/obdfilter-survey failed: 127&lt;/p&gt;</description>
